docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON's BIRTH-DAY IN BROOKLYN.--This day, in Brooklyn, was celebrated with more than usual eclat. At sunrise the stars and stripes were run up in every part of the city, and flaunted gaily to the balmy breeze of a morning more like Spring than Winter.

docs.lead_paragraph: Trial of Wm. M. Doty for Perjury. SEVENTH DAY. COURT OF GENERAL SESSIONS.--Tuesday.--Before Hon. Recorder TILLOU, Aldermen WESLEY SMITH and BARD.--The People agt. Wm. M. Doty.-On calling the names of the Jurors empaneled in this case, it was found that one of their number, Mr. JOHN OWENS, was unable to attend, from illness. A physician's certificate to that effect was handed in.

docs.lead_paragraph: UNITED STATES MAIL BAS FOUND.--Sergeant CUNLAN of the Third District Police, on Sunday evening found a United States Newspaper Mail bag in a lot, between Henry and Hicks, near Warren-street. It was filled with newspapers which had apparently never been unfolded. The mouth of the bag was tied with a single cord, and on one side was the United States stamp.

docs.lead_paragraph: The country papers are congratulating the city on the novelty which is said to have been introduced into sundry of our newly bail houses, in the shape of a room in the upper story, devoted to gymnastic exercise and recreation. The thought is, that now the son, or wealth need not look pale any longer-need not be thin, emaciated and dyspeptic.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Pacific United States mail steamship reached this port early yesterday morning, from Liverpool on the 9th instant. She has made the passage in a little over eleven days Her news is four days later, but there is very little of it. From France we have little of interest: from England nothing. Belgium is on the point of entering into closer relations with Russia.
